===Radio===
Hodgman has been a guest on a number of different radio programs including [[WBEZ|WBEZ's]] ''[[This American Life]]'',<ref>[http://www.thisamericanlife.org/radio-archives/episode/226/reruns ''Reruns'']</ref><ref>[http://www.thisamericanlife.org/radio-archives/episode/243/later-that-same-day ''Later That Same Day'']</ref> and ''[[The Sound of Young America]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maximumfun.org/blog/2006/10/podcast-best-friends-with-john-hodgman.html |title=The Sound of Young America: Podcast: Best Friends with John Hodgman and Jonathan Coulton |publisher=Maximumfun.org |date= |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref> [[WFMU|WFMU's]] ''[[The Best Show on WFMU]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wfmu.org/playlists/BS |title=The Best Show on WFMU Archives |publisher=Wfmu.org |date= |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref> [[NPR|NPR's]] ''[[Wait, Wait, Don't Tell Me]]'' and [[North Carolina Public Radio|North Carolina Public Radio's]] ''[[The State of Things (radio show)|The State of Things]]''.<ref>[http://wunc.org/tsot/archive/sot1026b.mp3/view Resident Expert John Hodgman talks with ''[[The State of Things (radio show)|The State of Things]]'' on [[North Carolina Public Radio]]]</ref> Hodgman has also been featured on several [[podcasts]] including occasional appearances as "[[Judge John Hodgman]]" on ''[[Jordan, Jesse, Go!]]'' which led to a stand-alone podcast<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maximumfun.org/2010/11/01/judge-john-hodgman-podcast |title=Judge John Hodgman: The Podcast |publisher=Maximum Fun |date= |accessdate=2011-02-23}}</ref> produced by [[Maximum Fun]]. Hodgman was also a guest alongside [[Jonathan Coulton]] on a number of episodes of ''You Look Nice Today''. Hodgman was also a guest on ''[[This Week In Tech]]'' with [[Leo Laporte]],<ref>{{cite web|author=Running time: 1:45:29 |url=http://twit.tv/167 |title=More TWiT Than You Require |publisher=Twit.tv |date= |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref> [[Stuff You Should Know]], and has been featured on the podcast ''[[Boing Boing#Boing Boing TV|Boing Boing TV]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jardin |first=Xeni |url=http://boingboing.net/2008/09/08/boing-boing-tv-john.html |title=BoingBoing TV with John Hodgman |publisher=Boingboing.net |date=2008-09-08 |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref>  Hodgman also appeared in person and on the NPR radio broadcast of ''City Arts and Lectures'', in a recorded interview by Dave Eggers, in front of a live studio audience on November 10, 2008, at the Herbst Theatre in [[San Francisco, California]]. He was a guest on [[Neil deGrasse Tyson]]'s radio show ''[[StarTalk Radio]]'' on February 27, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://startalkradio.net/2011/02/27/a-conversation-with-john-hodgman |title=A Conversation with John Hodgman |publisher=StarTalk Radio Show |date= |accessdate=2011-03-15}}</ref> He appeared again on City Arts and Lectures, in front of a live audience at the Nourse Theater, interviewing Adam Savage on May 29, 2013.

