=== Music ===
* Hodgman was featured on the track "Question and Answer Time" on [[MC Frontalot]]'s 2010 album ''[[Zero Day (album)|Zero Day]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://frontalot.com/0day_credz.txt |title=Track 12: John Hodgman '&#39;I'm not a rapper'&#39; |date= |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref>
* Hodgman has appeared in two indie music videos directed by [[Tom Scharpling]]. The first was [[Ted Leo & The Pharmacists]] "Bottled In Cork," followed by [[The New Pornographers]]' "Moves."

==In print==
[[File:John Hodgman BBF 2010 Shankbone.jpg|thumb|Hodgman at the 2010 [[Brooklyn Book Festival]].]]
As contributor:
* Hodgman appears on the cover of the February 2007 edition of ''[[Wired Magazine]],'' as a contributor to their "What we don't know about..." articles.
* Hodgman oversaw the "True Life Tales" section of the Sunday ''[[New York Times Magazine]].''<ref>The New York Times Magazine “[http://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/18/magazine/18funny_intro.html?ex=1284696000&en=30d4458e4bc553d9&ei=5090&partner=rssuserland&emc=rss From the Editors].” September 18, 2005.</ref> The section is currently on hiatus.
* Hodgman has guest written for the "Sedaratives" section of ''[[The Believer (magazine)|The Believer]]''. "Sedaratives" is an [[advice column]] created by [[Amy Sedaris]].
* Hodgman wrote the Massachusetts<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/ideas/articles/2008/09/28/massachusetts_bulwark_against_the_kingdom_of_the_anti_christ/ |title=Massachusetts: Bulwark against the Kingdom of the Anti Christ |publisher=Boston.com |date=2008-09-28 |accessdate=2011-04-04 |first=John |last=Hodgman}}</ref> chapter in the anthology ''[[State by State: A Panoramic Portrait of America]].''
* Hodgman wrote the introduction to ''The Laugh-Out-Loud Cats Sell Out'' (2009), a collection of Adam Koford's ''[[Hobotopia]]'' comic strips.
* Hodgman founded The Little Gray Book Lectures in [[Williamsburg, Brooklyn]].  The lectures have been on hiatus "for the foreseeable future" as of August 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.littlegraybooks.com/ |title=Little Gray Book Lectures, including archival material |publisher=Littlegraybooks.com |date= |accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref>
As author:
* ''[[The Areas of My Expertise]]'' (ISBN 0-525-94908-9, 2005)
* ''[[More Information Than You Require]]'' (ISBN 0-525-95034-6, October 2008)
* ''[[That Is All (2011 book)|That Is All]]'' (ISBN 978-0525952442, November 2011)

